Many people have been left injured while some residents fled after a gas plant went up in flames in a community in Rives state.  The explosion occurred in Rumuodomaya community, Obio/Akpo Local Government Area of Rivers State on Saturday night, Te PUNCH reports. The explosion occurred about 8:45 pm with a loud sound which caused panic among residents of the area with some fleeing their homes in fear. The cause of the explosion could not be immediately ascertained as of the time of filing this report. The PUNCH reports that this came barely three weeks after a gas leak at a facility operated by the Nigeria Liquefied Natural Gas (NLNG) in Elibrada, Emuoha Local Government Area of the state. Details later… Source By Ezra Musa Kaduna - A gas explosion on Saturday afternoon burnt down shops injuring several persons in Kaduna. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the incident occurred at about 2:00 pm on Kachia road by Anguwn Boro in Kaduna. NAN reports that some resident seen crying at… January 4, 2020 In "News" By Solomon Asowata Lagos -  The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) on Friday said that its impact assessment of Thursday’s explosion of a gas tanker in Iju area of Lagos had revealed that 44 persons sustained varying degrees of injuries in the incident. Mr Ibrahim Farinloye, Acting Zonal Coordinator, South… September 25, 2020 In "News" According to a report by The PUNCH, an explosion has rocked a gas station in the Baruwa community of the Alimosho Local Government Area of Lagos State. It was gathered that the incident occurred around 05:45am on Thursday. No casualty has been confirmed as of the time of filing this… October 8, 2020 In "News"